requirements for real-time languages.wreal-time languages have different requirementsfrom other programming languages because of the special nature of their applications, the environmentin which their object programs are executed and the environment in which they may be compiled.  itmay not be the language extensions that ultimately advance developments in the field.  progress may be madeby attacking the special compiling and executing system problems that must be solved.cacm march, opler, a.ca jb march ,   : am